<title>A Graphic Novel About the creation of the proof of van der Waerden's Theorem</title>

<introduction>
<title>Project by:  <em>Jinxiao Jin</em>, <em>Listiarini Listiarini</em>, <em>Tianqi Su</em>, and  <em>JiaWei Xie</em></title>
</introduction>
<p></p>
<p><m>\textbf{Summary:}</m> The main goal of this project is to use a graphic novel format to restore the event when van der
Waerden, Emil Artin, and Otto Schreier worked together to find the proof of Baudet's conjecture. </p>

<figure>
<caption>Emil Artin, Otto Schreier, and Bartel van der Waerden in 1926</caption>
<image source ="images/vdw_char_bw.jpg"/>
</figure>
<p>
Our script closely follows van der Waerden's description of the events that happened in 1926 in Artin's office in the Mathematics Department of the University of Hamburg. For more, please see B.L. van der Waerden, <q>How the proof of Baudet's conjecture was found.</q> In <em>Studies in
Pure Mathematics</em>, Edited by L . Mirsky, Academic Press, London, 1971, 251-260. Also, see A. Soifer,  2009. <em>The Mathematical Coloring Book</em>. Springer. Pages 110 - 121.
</p>
<p>Enjoy!</p>
